I think this expression is not very clear, as `\vec{x}` is not the same on the left and on the right if I understand correctly.

Could you clarify that `α` is not a generic type here: it has to be a product type for the construction to make sense. And that the measure is not a generic measure either: it has to be a product measure (more precisely, mu is not a measure on the product space, but a family of measure on each factor, right?)

Note that the notion of marginal in probability theory is also very important for measures which are not product measures. For your goal here (having a condition version of Fubini), assuming that the measure is a product measure is completely reasonable, but you should emphasize this prominently in the file-level docstring and also in the docstring of the definition.
